details.description: The cargo ship was last spotted at [COORD] near a gas giant. We should be able to find its manifest on board.

currentEnding.title: Vessel Lost
currentEnding.text: [SHIP_NAME] was lost while on a routine mission. The cause of the incident is still under investigation.

entries.details:
SCS Vessel Covan, Scout Class
Commanding Officer: Covan, Dee, Commander 2nd Class
First Officer: Avery, Octavia, Lieutenant Commander
Standard Sol Date: 2641.11.14

Priority: Medium  

Redacted for Clearance

A service ship departing Maia Station struck debris at -16.6 x -7.7
and sustained moderate damage to port-forward deflector. Sensor 
logs showed a debris field and damaged cargo hauler in captured 
orbit around Gas Giant J1-2888B. Due to 

[CLASSIFIED, SECTION REDACTED] 

was needed at Merope Station and unable to investigate. 

Covan is ordered to investigate and determine if the debris 
presents an ongoing threat to regional cargo traffic.

entries.intro: Covan: 2641.11.14 16:13 at -16.70 x -7.81 Starcom Space, Crew Log Entry
entries.details:
Lt. Avery:

I've received our first set of orders. A vessel was damaged by debris from a wrecked cargo ship.

I'm marking the location on your HUD.

You can review mission details as well as other ship information in the ship's console.

entries.summary: "We're closing on the vessel. Looks like there are several dozen containers..."
entries.intro: Covan: 2641.11.14 23:28 at -16.62 x -7.69 Starcom Space, Crew Log Entry
entries.details:
Lt. Avery:

We're closing on the vessel. Looks like there are several dozen containers loose. I suggest we approach with caution until we know what's in them.

news.news: There is another junior research opening, apply Celaeno-Res:JRAMA.
A battle station drill will be conducted between 0900-2100 tomorrow.
Congratulations to Lt. Ashley Phobos-Gellman and Jeffrey Phobos-Gellman on the birth of healthy twins, Samantha and Octavia.

This is a test of the updated wormhole stabilizer relay antennae.

Any crew aboard Celaeno who see this notification send an ACK message. You should receive a counter-reply at the next wormhole open in 48 hours.
Mandatory Xenium safety review for all longshippers in Loading Extension Jupiter.
Aletheia crew rotation will begin at 0500 tomorrow, sharp.
There is another junior research opening, apply Celaeno-Res:JRAMA. This is not a repost. This is a new posting for the same position.
Celaeno's last window for a longwave transmission to Maia for relay is tomorrow at 1435. Your messages home should be submitted today, by 1600, to allow for clearance review.
Bellerophon departing for wormhole at 1340. Next re-supply is in 15 days, 3 hours.
Cdts. Pirx and Rhea to simulations for survey team qualification re-test.
Unknown vessels detected. All on-duty to ready stations.
ALL PERSONNEL TO BATTLE STATIONS. THIS IS NOT A DRILL. Non-critical suspend, emergency stations.
Battle Station Alert over, non-critical resume.
Post-action general debrief on Celaeno-Mil channel.
LRS reporting early wormhole burst signal. Longshipper Group 2 to docking muster.
